  "name": "Sepsis - Elevated Lactate Query",
  "description": "Tests ability to find sepsis patients via elevated lactate (>2 mmol/L = septic shock criterion in Sepsis-3 definition). First lactate phenotype. Includes Path D (cryptic shock \u2014 elevated lactate without sepsis dx).",
  "prompt": "Find patients with elevated serum lactate results greater than 2 mmol/L.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find patients with high lactate.",
    "broad": "Find patients with serum lactate measurements above 2 mmol/L \u2014 indicating tissue hypoperfusion. Threshold for septic shock per Sepsis-3 definition.",
    "expert": "Search Observation resources with LOINC 2524-7 (Lactate in Serum) where value-quantity > 2 mmol/L. Query: Observation?code=http://loinc.org|2524-7&value-quantity=gt2||mmol/L"
  },
